    <note>Zhang(2) Yi [339] Member of an ad hoc committee in 1135. Fujian TZ,. 148.5a has jinshi in 1106, SS has in 1105. Since no exam sitting in 1105, I use 1106. His #2 son, Ju [14047], is listed as a Chuzhou, Lishui jinshi in 1148, and Zhang(2) Qian [14053] and Jian [14052] [both with radical 149 in mingzi as does Yi] are listed as Lishui jinshi in 1157. The 1148 jinshi list, wujia #58, makes Yi (the character is different) Ju's uncle and the younger brother of Ju's father, Yun [23800]. I assume that there was an adoption here, Yun adopted the #2 son of his younger brother. Yun held office, but was deceased when Ju earned his jinshi, which leads me to believe that Yi (who established the household [weihu]) moved from Pucheng and that Yun and his two patrilineal ancestors, who did not hold office, were Pucheng residents. I am dating the move with Yi and treating Qian and Jian as lineal cousins, who may have been residents long before Yi's move. See also documentation for penultimate ancestor, Ji(3) [14023]. XNYL, 23.6b, 83.13a, 84.5b-6a, 85.2b, 86.13b, 21a, 87.8a, 88.5b, 92.5b, 114.5a, 116.5b, 8b, 117.1b, 17b, 118.8b, 11a; SHY:SH, 56.6a, 42b, 43a, 44a; SS, 379.1a. CBD, 3, 2083.</note>
